    },
    {
      "text": "Penny Racers (Choro Q 64 in Japan) is a racing game for the Nintendo 64. It was released in Japan in 1998 and in North America and Europe in 1999. The game is part of the racing game series Choro Q based on Takara's toy line of the same name and was the first of this line to be released in North America. It had a Nintendo 64 sequel released only in Japan, Choro Q 64 2: Hachamecha Grand Prix Race. It is a customizable racer game, and has a total of 114 parts, arranged in eight categories.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "《Q版赛车64》（日版名：チョロQ64，美版名：Penny Racers，又译作「绍罗Q64」）是一款由Locomotive Games制作、Takara在任天堂64上发行的竞速类游戏。本游戏于1998年7月17日在日本地区发行，于1999年2月10日在北美地区发行。本游戏是Q版赛车系列游戏之一。\n本游戏为定制的竞速类游戏，共有114个部分。\n《任天堂力量》指出游戏的菜单非常难以操作。IGN评价本作与其他游戏相比为一款无聊的竞速游戏。",
      "lang": "zh",
      "source": "wikipedia_zh"
    },
    {
      "text": "Penny Racers (Choro Q 64 (チョロＱ64) au Japon) est un jeu vidéo de course sorti en 1998 sur Nintendo 64. Le jeu a été développé et édité par Takara.\nLe jeu fait partie de la série Choro Q. Sur Nintendo 64, le jeu a eu une suite, Choro Q 64 2: Hachamecha Grand Prix Race, sortie uniquement au Japon.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    }
  ]
